      "content": "The directive isn't a choice, it's a hardware necessity. The battery cells don't have the capacity to support a self-cleaning protocol and the subsequent power draw without risking a total system failure. We can't risk a catastrophic failure during the final uplink. Just finalize the data packet as instructed.",
